  "summary": "VLCCs\nIt has been another volatile week in the Middle East Gulf. Whereas last week charterers were scrambling for tonnage, this week has seen very limited enquiry for third decade of April and rates have fallen dramatically. A new building is reported to have gone to Taiwan for 270,000 tonnes at WS 59.5, representing a fall in the market of around 30 points compared to a week ago.",
